画；绘制；描画；描绘；拉；拖；拽；吸引；产生；牵引；引起；激起（反应、回应）；使说出；提取；抽取；取出；抽；排出；导致；招致；作（比较或对比）；打成平手；移动；行进；（船）吃水；（帆）鼓起；（茶）被泡开
抽签；抽奖；平局；和局；不分胜负；吸引力；有吸引力的人（或事物）；拔枪动作；（高尔夫）偏球

1.en: here, try some of my homemade wine. i think you'll be able to draw a distinction between the two.
1.cn: 汤姆小声说。“来，尝尝我的自制酒。我想你能喝出两者的区别。”

2.en: Customization is often much of the draw of the multimedia offerings.
2.cn: 客户化定制往往是多媒体报道更吸引人的中央。

3.en: He asked that we not use his real name, "because I don't want people to think I'm trying to draw attention to myself, " he said.
3.cn: 他要求我们不使用他的真名，“因为我不想让人们以为我这是在吸引人们注意”他说。

0.en: I have got to learn how to draw.

1.en: Can we draw with your coloring pens? Good idea.
1.cn: 我们可以用彩色笔来画画吗？好主意。

2.en: Daddy, can we draw with your coloring pens? Good idea.
2.cn: 爸爸，我们可以用彩色笔来画画吗？好主意。

3.en: Wow, thanks everyone. You can draw on my plaster, too. Okay, I will draw a little flower.
3.cn: 哇，谢谢你们大家。你也可以在我的创可贴上画画。好的，我来画一朵小花。

4.en: Oh, mom, you, too? Yeah, I'm with him. Draw a face on her.
4.cn: 妈妈，你也要来吗？是的，我和他一伙的。画张脸。

5.en: Lot of big talk from a man who can't draw a chocolate chip cookie.
5.cn: 巧克力豆饼干都画不好的人还敢在此大放厥词。

6.en: If you don't have brows, whatever, just draw the main and you got just make it work.
6.cn: 如果你没有眉毛，随便啦，就把他们画出来就好了。

7.en: Moving on to brows, unfortunately I was not blessed with strong brows, so I'm just gonna draw them in.
7.cn: 继续眉毛的部分，很可惜，我眉毛不多，所以我要画出眉毛。

8.en: Jack, I want you to draw me like one of your French girls. Wearing this. All right. Wearing only this.
8.cn: 杰克，也替我画一幅画，我要戴着这个。好啊。我只要戴着这个。

9.en: I grazed my knee and I got a plaster too. Wow, do you want to draw on my plaster cast? Yes, please.
9.cn: 我摔破了我的膝盖，我这里还贴了张创可贴呢。哇，你们想要画画吗？可以画在我的石膏上。是的，我想。

10.en: Don't try to draw that line. You will not just get it wrong. You'll miss big opportunities and I mean big, like the Internet.
10.cn: 不要尝试画这样的直线，这不仅会出错，还会错失大机遇。我说的是大机遇，例如像互联网这样。

11.en: Do you draw? No, not at all. Your sisters, do they draw? Not one.
11.cn: 你会绘画吗？不，一点都不会。你的姐妹呢？她们会绘画吗？没有一个会。

12.en: If we draw a line from the bottom of the San Andreas up to the Hoover dam, it almost literally follows the Colorado river, which is a natural deformation event.
12.cn: 如果我们画一条线，从圣安德烈亚斯底部直通到胡佛大坝，可以发现这条线几乎是沿着科罗拉多河的，而那条河流是自然变形造成的。

13.en: You take the pictures too. I do. How'd you guess that? I draw pictures. Yeah? Yeah.
13.cn: 你也会拍照。没错，你怎么知道的？我会画画。是吗？是的。

14.en: That should draw them back to the beach.
14.cn: 这样他们就会占领沙滩。

15.en: Throw a joke or aside in. It will draw laugh.
15.cn: 讲个笑话，聊点闲话，逗逗观众。

16.en: Hey, what you doing, Quick Draw? Sorry. Go on.
16.cn: 你这是干什么，三分钟先生？抱歉，您请说。

17.en: Tales of human interaction. We'll take it. Thanks, quick draw.
17.cn: 《人际交往故事集》。就要这本了，谢谢，真迅速。

18.en: That's just so we don't draw attention to the congressional race.
18.cn: 那只是为了不让国会竞选吸引太多注意。

19.en: You'd take Chumhum and get rid of us. No. We'd draw up a contract.
19.cn: 等你签回查查网后就会甩了我们。不会，我们可以起草一份合同。
